there are three different vip classes, named "商务座" (business class), "观光座" (sightseeing class) and "特等座" (deluxe class). unlike on airliners, 商务座 (business class) is in fact better than "一等座" (first class) on crh trains. 商务座 (business class) and 观光座 (sightseeing class) priced the same, while 特等座 is usually more expensive than "一等座" (first class), but cheaper than 商务座 and 观光座. train tickets[edit] chinese train ticket with fields description at the point where a given train starts, train tickets can usually be bought up to seven days in advance. after the point where a given train starts, a small number of 